  "strongest_result": "T507 turns the finality residual into a two-stage finite gate. First, the admissible operation algebra decides whether the mirror difference is recoverable: positivity-preserving/block-diagonal operations recover nothing, while full-Krein collective boosts recover a mirror difference. Second, the normalization rule decides whether a recovered physical mirror can still be hidden: full-space Born normalization leaks mirror weight into W+-restricted statistics, while self-normalized/projector Born hides it. The hidden-record reading is therefore only a review target in the double-special Krein-retention plus self-normalized corner; the default positivity/BRST plus full-Born corner remains redundancy."
